│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                             │
│                                                                                         │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                                         │
│ ### 1. Understanding the Issue ###                                                      │
│ The assertion failure occurs in `llvm::LoopVectorizationPlanner::computeBestVF` at line │
│ 7378. The assertion checks that the vectorization factor (VF) chosen by the VPlan-based │
│ cost model matches the VF chosen by the legacy cost model, or that the VPlan contains   │
│ additional simplifications not accounted for in the legacy cost model.                  │
│                                                                                         │
│ ### 2. Analyzing `opt`'s Log ###                                                        │
│ The log indicates that the disagreement between the VPlan-based and legacy cost models  │
│ is the root cause. The VPlan-based cost model selects a scalar VF (Width = 1), while    │
│ the legacy cost model selects a vector VF (Width = 4). The function                     │
│ `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` is supposed to verify if the VPlan contains     │
│ extra simplifications, but it is not resolving correctly in the debugger.               │
│                                                                                         │
│ ### 3. Root Cause Analysis ###                                                          │
│ The issue lies in the assertion logic. The VPlan-based cost model and legacy cost model │
│ disagree on the optimal VF, and the function `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications`    │
│ does not provide a valid resolution. This indicates that the VPlan-based cost model may │
│ not be accounting for all relevant factors, or the legacy cost model is overestimating  │
│ the benefits of vectorization.                                                          │
│                                                                                         │
│ ### 4. Proposed Edit Points ###                                                         │
│ To address the issue, the assertion at lines 7378-7381 in                               │
│ `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp` should be modified to log a warning   │
│ instead of aborting the program. This will allow the optimization process to continue   │
│ while highlighting the discrepancy for further investigation.                           │
│                                                                                         │
│ ### 5. Conclusion ###                                                                   │
│ The proposed fix ensures that the optimization process does not terminate prematurely   │
│ due to a disagreement between cost models. This change will help identify and address   │
│ the root cause of the discrepancy without disrupting the overall compilation process.   │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                                         │
